snippet.textDisplay: Ben Zinnar Ah, yes. Not to forget batch production. So basically you shoot a bunch of videos in a day, edit a bunch of videos another day, and then upload them according to schedule. If you keep a backlog of videos ready, you can maintain this technique while also ensuring daily uploads. :) Can upload them together too if you want (as unlisted). Then when it's time to roll out one of the videos, simply make it public and promote the video.

So basically you shoot a bunch of videos in a day, edit a bunch of videos another day, and then upload them according to schedule. snippet.textDisplay:
I'm thinking the key to daily videos is efficiency. You may be able to develop that as you make more videos. Basically, cut down on time wherever you can. From pre-production to production to post-production.

It will probably also help to pre-plan videos in advance. For example, knowing what you're going to do for the next two or three videos beforehand.

The other thing may be just to be spontaneous, though this may affect quality depending on your ability and what kind of video you're making.

But to make good quality daily videos, you'll probably require a good amount of time. But if quality isn't too much of an issue, then can take less time. :)
